	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories One child has reportedly died after a bus carrying schoolchildren rolled onto its side on the R555 near Laersdrift, Mpumalanga, on Sunday. According to a Facebook post by Specialised Investigation PSTT, the bus was travelling from Steelpoort to Middelburg when the accident happened. It is unclear what led to the bus rolling over. Netwerk24 quoted an unnamed sourced who confirmed the incident, saying that learners from HTS Middelburg were on the bus, among others. The source could not confirm the death of a learner and police could not be reached for comment. More information will be added as it becomes available. This is a developing story. @TrafficSA . Schoolbus accident on the R555 towards Stofberg to Middelburg. Services on scene.One under bus. Please drive careful bad rainy condition. https://t.co/Kd9dkZw49s pic.twitter.com/jRbILDSv2y  Apparently there's a bus accident in Laersdrift and it was full of children who were going back to boarding school. One child was confirmed dead on the scene ??????      24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.